						               													<description>Originally published in 1983, Samurai Lords has been enjoyed by Japanese for decades and remains to this day, the Japanese gamer's strategic game of choice for simulating the most turbulent period in Japanese history. Now MMP is proud to offer for the first time this remarkable game to the English-speaking world.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players scheme, plot, plan, fight, and deal with unforeseen events in the quest to become the supreme Samurai on the land. With 26 scenarios to represent periods ranging from the 12th to the 16th century and with some 500 major samurai that vied for power during this the long period of civil war individually represented, players will gain a unique insight into the inner workings of feudal Japan.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is by far the most comprehensive game on Japanese history ever published.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Samurai Lords scale:&amp;#10;Game Turn: 1 year&amp;#10;Counters: Individual Leaders and 1000 men per strength point&amp;#10;Map: Area map representing feudal Japan&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Samurai Lords Game Details:&amp;#10;Players: 1-16 (9-16 requires two copies)&amp;#10;Scenarios: 30+&amp;#10;Complexity: Medium &amp;#10;Playing Time: 1 to 20 hours&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Samurai Lords was designed by Yukihiro Kuroda. English development by Adam Starkweather, with graphic arts by Mark Mahaffey.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
